summary: Some of my favourite lyrics by Kim Namjoon
title: Some of my favourite lyrics by Kim Namjoon
body:
Spring Day: Honestly I miss you, but I’ll erase you//‘Cause it hurts less than to blame you

Spring Day: You know it all, you’re my best friend//The morning will come again//No darkness, no season is eternal

Cypher, Pt 4: “Oh, face not an idol..” Sorry bae

Reflection: The world is just another name for despair// … I am all of my joy and anxiety

Baepsae: They said, “my legs are worth a million dollars”//Mine are short, how can you do the same events//They say, if it’s the same meadow, it’s it okay

Change: Kill people with fingers on Twitter//More than a gun, more than a knife//The tip of your tongue just glitter

Sea: Where there is hope, there is always despair//We need to be in despair, for all our hardships (this song fucks me up)

Champion: What’s wrong with the life of a passenger//If somebody gotta be, then I'mma be the messenger//I’m just too young, don’t know what to believe in//But too young, you know, not to be living

Anpanman: To be honest, I’m scared of falling//And of letting you down//But, even if it takes up all my strength//I will be sure that I stay by your side (it’s such a happy song with such a tragic meaning)

Outro: Tear: Stop saying things like forever, forever//After all, the end originally exists

Ddaeng: Frogs who live up to your name, I hope you die in that well. (Being a frog in a well is a popular Korean idiom. It’s based off a story about a frog that believes that the well it lives in is the entire world.)

Trivia 承: Love:  It’s a long way from I to U//Fuck, JKLMNOPQRST//I crossed all the letters and I reached you (all of trivia 承: love, really)

The Truth Untold: Because I can’t get closer to you//There’s no name you can call me (another song that fucks me up)

Fake Love: I wish love was perfect as love itself//… I grew a flower that can’t be bloomed in a dream that can’t come true.

Idol: You call me artist. You call me idol//No matter what you call me. I don’t care.

Waste It On Me: Treat me like a comma, I’ll take you to a new phrase. (Get me with that grammar analogy)

tokyo: Life is a word that sometimes you cannot say//And ash is a thing that someday we all should be//… Why do love and hate sound just the same to me?

seoul: And the Han River that bears too much Han(1)//… And the kids all grown up, and me who’s a little late

moonchild: We gotta dance in the rain//Dance in the pain//Even though we crash down//We gon dance in the plane

moonchild: It’s okay to shed the tears, but don’t you tear yourself

everythingoes: And everyday I stay//Since both people and pain will all die one day

forever rain: When it rains I get a little feeling that I do have a friend//Keeps knocking on my windows, asks me if I’m doing well//And I answer, I’m still a hostage of life//I don’t live because I can’t die, but I’m chained to something (this entire song is such a masterpiece and it makes sob)

title: Mono songs as things
body:
TOKYO: early morning train rides, desert gas stations, the low murmur of sea waves, watching the sun rise, writing letters by hand

SEOUL: driving in a busy city, having a beer with close friends, listening to your favorite song on the radio, skyscrapers, breathing in smog and coughing, eating at fast food chains

MOONCHILD: staying awake late at night, holding back tears, taking pictures of the moon, solitude, walking alone under the moonlight, writing in a secret diary, sleeping with earbuds on

BADBYE: puffy eyes after hours of crying, eating fingernails, smeared makeup, broken heart, resignation, knowing that it will pass

UHGOOD: gritting teeth, studying in a quiet library, frustration, a cassette mixtape, having a playlist for every mood, the calm after the storm, empty school classrooms, smiling even when you can't

EVERYTHING GOES: breakfast in bed, the safety of an embrace, laughing hard after a bad day, "it will be better", the golden hour, hot chocolate on a rainy day, starting again  

FOREVER RAIN: walking under the rain without an umbrella, people watching, sleeping in, the smell of wet grass, wandering without a destination, the comfort of being alone, loving yourself despite everything
